A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Chapter 4 of Title 1 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 holidays and observances, so as to designate the month of April each year as "Black
3 Women's History Month" in Georgia; to provide for legislative findings; to provide for
4 ceremonies and programs; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for
5 other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Chapter 4 of Title 1 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to holidays and
9 observances, is amended by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
10 "1-4-27.
11 (a) The General Assembly hereby finds and determines that:
12 (1) The State of Georgia takes great pride in celebrating Black Women's History Month,
13 a celebration that is designed to recognize and applaud the achievements of African
14 American women;
15 (2) Generations of Black women throughout American history have used their
16 intelligence, imagination, sense of wonder, and tenacity to make extraordinary
