17 contributions to not only the State of Georgia, but also to the everyday means of how
18 Georgians live;
19 (3) The State of Georgia is home to many women of talent who represent a remarkable
20 range of accomplishments in a wide diversity of specialties, including the arts, literature,
21 film, and television; science and technology; news media; jurisprudence and government;
22 and education;
23 (4) These women's lives and works span the centuries of American history and come
24 from a variety of different cultural and ethnic backgrounds;
25 (5) The State of Georgia is proud to honor all women seeking to advance in all of the
26 important areas of life's work; and
27 (6) There is a need for public education, awareness, and discourse to address the impacts
28 Black women have had and continue to have on the State of Georgia and all its people.
29 (b) The month of April each year is designated as 'Black Women's History Month' in
30 Georgia.
31 (c) Officials and departments of state, county, and municipal governments, boards of
32 education, elementary and secondary schools, colleges and universities, businesses, and all
33 citizens are encouraged to participate in appropriate ceremonies, programs, and activities
34 that commemorate and honor the contributions of Black women throughout each April
35 during Black Women's History Month."
36 SECTION 2.
37 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
